    <summary>Your PC in VR</summary>
    <description>Watch movies, browse the web or play games on a giant virtual screen.</description>
    <releaseNotes>
      Release Notes - Version 1.26.4
      - Added subtitle support with streamed videos
      - Added keyboard shortcuts to switch monitor and toggle VR mode
      - Added VoiceMeeter compatibility option in Streamer window
      - Improved head/controller prediction on Pico
      - Improved spacewarp (SSW) quality by increasing the motion vector resolution on Quest 2 and Quest Pro
      - Improved resolution of portrait monitors
      - Added Swedish and Irish keyboard layouts
      - Added Processor/memory information in the About tab
      - Increased disconnection time after removing headset from 1 to 5 minutes
      - Fixed timewarp layer positioning in some VR games
      - Fixed video download queue when cancelling a download
      - Fixed rare issue with random windows opening after connecting
      - Fixed rare issue where desktop would not appear after connecting
      - Fixed long press to always trigger contextual menu in Windows
      - Fixed compatibility issues with Remote Desktop
      - Fixed keyboard positioning so that it doesn't overlap the screen
      - Fixed issue with app exiting when connecting/disconnecting a bluetooth keyboard/mouse on Pico
      - Fixed bluetooth mouse input on macOS
      - Fixed compatibility with: Space Engine, Hitman 3, Grapple Tournament


      Not all games are compatible with Virtual Desktop.

      Additional Notes
      You can launch games that aren't part of your Oculus or Steam library by right-clicking the Streamer icon, selecting "Launch Game..." and locating the executable. Alternatively, you can inject games through a batch file (.bat) by using: VirtualDesktop.Streamer.exe "[ExecutablePath]"    
    </releaseNotes>
